        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 3:11PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 307 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a large area of rain with
embedded thunder across central mountains west of Buena Vista and
Nathrop. This area of rain was moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Locally heavy rain, gusty winds and possible small hail

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...High water is likely to occur in creeks and streams west of
the Buena Vista and Nathrop area.

Locations impacted include...
Cottonwood Pass, Alpine, and St Elmo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
